RagTuff — Executive Buyer Summary

RagTuff is a Strategically, Financially, and Cryptographically Engineered Decision-Support Positioning System designed for defensive and adversarial analysis, counter-improvement measurement, and consequence modeling under uncertainty.

RagTuff is advisory-only by design. It does not execute transactions, hold assets, control systems, or exercise authority. All outputs are analytical recommendations intended to support human decision-makers, who retain full responsibility and execution control at all times.

What RagTuff Is
	•	A decision-support and analytical positioning system
	•	A modeling environment for stress, adversarial pressure, and scenario evaluation
	•	A non-custodial, non-executing, non-authoritative analytical framework
	•	A tool for understanding consequences before action is taken

What RagTuff Is Not
	•	Not an automated trading system
	•	Not an asset manager, broker, custodian, or fiduciary
	•	Not an execution engine or control system
	•	Not financial, legal, or investment advice
	•	Not a substitute for human judgment or governance

Core Capabilities
	•	Scenario and consequence modeling across financial and cryptographic systems
	•	Adversarial and defensive posture analysis
	•	Counter-improvement and adaptation measurement
	•	Decision positioning under uncertainty and stress conditions

Design and Risk Posture
	•	Advisory-only outputs
	•	No custody, no key management, no transaction signing
	•	No autonomous execution
	•	Human-in-the-loop by default
	•	Designed to reduce risk, not transfer it

Intended Users
	•	Enterprises and institutions
	•	Security, risk, and strategy teams
	•	Advanced individual operators requiring analytical foresight
	•	Organizations operating in complex, adversarial, or volatile environments

Commercial Model
RagTuff is licensed as software infrastructure, not as a managed service.
Licensing grants the right to use the system for internal analytical purposes, subject to strict non-execution and non-custodial constraints.
